{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880101960,"sessionID":"ses_2854c6defffeP8kJpwKqyO4d3V","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab3cb72001Cr1GDC74DTPrCt","messageID":"msg_d7ab3b6a1001axoBL0DzZus01C","sessionID":"ses_2854c6defffeP8kJpwKqyO4d3V","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ae9775401efc45009ab81740","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-030 Helm Chart Templates and Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the AgentCube Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`). The chart packages and deploys all AgentCube control plane components including Router, WorkloadManager, and optional Volcano Agent Scheduler with support for multi-environment configurations.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Chart Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: manifests/charts/base/\n13: ├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata (apiVersion, name, version)\n14: ├── values.yaml                         # Configuration values tree\n15: ├── .helmignore                         # Packaging exclusion patterns\n16: ├── crds/\n17: │   ├── agentruntime.yaml               # AgentRuntime CRD (existing)\n18: │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml            # CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n19: └── templates/\n20:     ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helper functions\n21:     ├── redis-secret.yaml               # Redis password Secret\n22:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml            # WorkloadManager Deployment + Service\n23:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml           # Router Deployment + Service\n24:     ├── rbac/\n25:     │   └── workloadmanager.yaml        # WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n26:     ├── rbac-router.yaml                # Optional Router RBAC\n27:     └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano Scheduler\n28: ```\n29: \n30: ### Component Diagram\n31: \n32: ```\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                    Helm Chart (agentcube)                        │\n35: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n36:                               │\n37:                               │ helm install/upgrade\n38:                               ▼\n39: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                   Kubernetes Cluster                             │\n41: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐ │\n42: │  │     Router       │  │ WorkloadManager  │  │   Volcano     │ │\n43: │  │  Deployment      │  │   Deployment     │  │   Scheduler   │ │\n44: │  │  + Service       │  │   + Service      │  │  (optional)   │ │\n45: │  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └───────────────┘ │\n46: │           │                      │                               │\n47: │           └──────────┬───────────┘                               │\n48: │                      │                                           │\n49: │           ┌──────────▼───────────┐                               │\n50: │           │   Redis Secret        │                               │\n51: │           │   (password store)    │                               │\n52: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n53: │                                                                   │\n54: │           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n55: │           │   RBAC Resources      │                               │\n56: │           │   (SA, Role, Binding) │                               │\n57: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n58: │                                                                   │\n59: │           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n60: │           │      CRDs             │                               │\n61: │           │  agentruntimes,       │                               │\n62: │           │  codeinterpreters     │                               │\n63: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n64: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ### Integration Points\n68: \n69: - **Redis**: External dependency for session storage (address/password from values)\n70: - **Volcano Scheduler**: Optional component for advanced scheduling\n71: - **RBAC**: WorkloadManager requires cluster-wide permissions; Router RBAC is optional\n72: - **CRDs**: AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n73: \n74: ## Data Structures\n75: \n76: ### Chart.yaml Metadata\n77: \n78: ```yaml\n79: apiVersion: v1\n80: name: agentcube\n81: description: A Helm chart for AgentCube\n82: version: 0.1.0\n83: appVersion: \"1.0.0\"\n84: keywords:\n85:   - agent\n86:   - sandbox\n87:   - kubernetes\n88:   - volcano\n89: maintainers:\n90:   - name: Volcano Authors\n91:     email: volcano-sh@googlegroups.com\n92: home: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n93: sources:\n94:   - https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ### values.yaml Configuration Tree\n98: \n99: ```yaml\n100: # Global settings\n101: imagePullSecrets: []\n102: nameOverride: \"\"\n103: fullnameOverride: \"\"\n104: \n105: # Redis configuration (required)\n106: redis:\n107:   addr: \"\"           # Required: Redis address (e.g., \"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\")\n108:   password: \"\"       # Optional: Redis password for authentication\n109: \n110: # Router component\n111: router:\n112:   replicas: 1\n113:   image:\n114:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router\n115:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n116:     tag: \"latest\"\n117:   service:\n118:     type: ClusterIP\n119:     port: 8080\n120:     targetPort: 8080\n121:   resources:\n122:     limits:\n123:       cpu: 500m\n124:       memory: 512Mi\n125:     requests:\n126:       cpu: 100m\n127:       memory: 128Mi\n128:   config: {}                      # Additional container configuration\n129:   extraEnv: []                    # Additional environment variables\n130:   serviceAccountName: \"\"          # Empty for default/auto-generated\n131:   rbac:\n132:     create: false                 # Disable RBAC by default\n133: \n134: # WorkloadManager component\n135: workloadmanager:\n136:   replicas: 1\n137:   image:\n138:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager\n139:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n140:     tag: \"latest\"\n141:   service:\n142:     type: ClusterIP\n143:     port: 8080\n144:   resources:\n145:     limits:\n146:       cpu: 500m\n147:       memory: 512Mi\n148:     requests:\n149:       cpu: 100m\n150:       memory: 128Mi\n151:   extraEnv: []                    # Additional environment variables\n152: \n153: # Volcano Scheduler (optional)\n154: volcano:\n155:   scheduler:\n156:     enabled: false                # Disabled by default\n157:     replicas: 1\n158:     image:\n159:       repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler\n160:       pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n161:       tag: \"latest\"\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ### Environment Variables\n165: \n166: | Variable | Component | Description | Source |\n167: |----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\n168: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Namespace from downward API | `fieldRef: metadata.namespace` |\n169: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis connection address | `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}` |\n170: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis authentication | `Secret {{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password` |\n171: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | Constructed: `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}` |\n172: \n173: ## API Contracts\n174: \n175: ### Template Contracts\n176: \n177: #### WorkloadManager Deployment\n178: \n179: ```yaml\n180: apiVersion: apps/v1\n181: kind: Deployment\n182: metadata:\n183:   name: workloadmanager\n184:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n185:   labels:\n186:     app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager\n187:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n188: spec:\n189:   replicas: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}\n190:   selector:\n191:     matchLabels:\n192:       app: workloadmanager\n193:   template:\n194:     metadata:\n195:       labels:\n196:         app: workloadmanager\n197:     spec:\n198:       serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\n199:       containers:\n200:       - name: workloadmanager\n201:         image: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\n202:         imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}\n203:         args:\n204:         - --port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n205:         - --runtime-class-name=\n206:         env:\n207:         - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n208:           valueFrom:\n209:             fieldRef:\n210:               fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n211:         - name: REDIS_ADDR\n212:           value: {{ .Values.redis.addr }}\n213:         - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n214:           valueFrom:\n215:             secretKeyRef:\n216:               name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis\n217:               key: password\n218:         - name: {{ .name }}\n219:           value: {{ .value }}\n220:         # ... extraEnv injected here\n221:         ports:\n222:         - name: http\n223:           containerPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n224:           protocol: TCP\n225:         livenessProbe:\n226:           httpGet:\n227:             path: /health\n228:             port: http\n229:           initialDelaySeconds: 10\n230:           periodSeconds: 10\n231:         readinessProbe:\n232:           httpGet:\n233:             path: /health\n234:             port: http\n235:           initialDelaySeconds: 5\n236:           periodSeconds: 5\n237:         resources: {{ toYaml .Values.workloadmanager.resources | nindent 10 }}\n238: ```\n239: \n240: #### Router Deployment\n241: \n242: ```yaml\n243: apiVersion: apps/v1\n244: kind: Deployment\n245: metadata:\n246:   name: agentcube-router\n247:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n248:   labels:\n249:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router\n250:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n251: spec:\n252:   replicas: {{ .Values.router.replicas }}\n253:   selector:\n254:     matchLabels:\n255:       app: agentcube-router\n256:   template:\n257:     metadata:\n258:       labels:\n259:         app: agentcube-router\n260:     spec:\n261:       {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n262:       serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n263:       {{- end }}\n264:       containers:\n265:       - name: agentcube-router\n266:         image: {{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\n267:         imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}\n268:         args:\n269:         - --port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n270:         - --debug\n271:         env:\n272:         - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n273:           valueFrom:\n274:             fieldRef:\n275:               fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n276:         - name: REDIS_ADDR\n277:           value: {{ .Values.redis.addr }}\n278:         - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n279:           valueFrom:\n280:             secretKeyRef:\n281:               name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis\n282:               key: password\n283:         - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n284:           value: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"\n285:         # ... extraEnv injected here\n286:         ports:\n287:         - name: http\n288:           containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n289:           protocol: TCP\n290:         livenessProbe:\n291:           httpGet:\n292:             path: /health/live\n293:             port: http\n294:           initialDelaySeconds: 1\n295:           periodSeconds: 2\n296:         readinessProbe:\n297:           httpGet:\n298:             path: /health/ready\n299:             port: http\n300:           initialDelaySeconds: 1\n301:           periodSeconds: 2\n302:         resources: {{ toYaml .Values.router.resources | nindent 10 }}\n303: ```\n304: \n305: #### WorkloadManager RBAC\n306: \n307: ```yaml\n308: # ServiceAccount\n309: apiVersion: v1\n310: kind: ServiceAccount\n311: metadata:\n312:   name: workloadmanager\n313:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n314: \n315: # ClusterRole\n316: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n317: kind: ClusterRole\n318: metadata:\n319:   name: workloadmanager\n320: rules:\n321: # Sandbox management\n322: - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n323:   resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n324:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n325: \n326: # Extension resources\n327: - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n328:   resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n329:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n330: \n331: # Warm pool status update\n332: - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n333:   resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n334:   verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n335: \n336: # CodeInterpreter management\n337: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n338:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n339:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n340: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n341:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n342:   verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n343: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n344:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n345:   verbs: [\"update\"]\n346: \n347: # AgentRuntime management\n348: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n349:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n350:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n351: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n352:   resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n353:   verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n354: \n355: # Pod read access\n356: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n357:   resources: [\"pods\"]\n358:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n359: \n360: # Token review for authentication\n361: - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n362:   resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n363:   verbs: [\"create\"]\n364: \n365: # Secret management\n366: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n367:   resources: [\"secrets\"]\n368:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n369: \n370: # ClusterRoleBinding\n371: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n372: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n373: metadata:\n374:   name: workloadmanager\n375: roleRef:\n376:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n377:   kind: ClusterRole\n378:   name: workloadmanager\n379: subjects:\n380: - kind: ServiceAccount\n381:   name: workloadmanager\n382:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n383: ```\n384: \n385: #### Router RBAC (Optional)\n386: \n387: Rendered only when `router.rbac.create: true`:\n388: \n389: ```yaml\n390: # ServiceAccount\n391: apiVersion: v1\n392: kind: ServiceAccount\n393: metadata:\n394:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n395:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n396: \n397: # Role (namespace-scoped)\n398: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n399: kind: Role\n400: metadata:\n401:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n402:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n403: rules:\n404: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n405:   resources: [\"secrets\"]\n406:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n407: \n408: # RoleBinding\n409: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n410: kind: RoleBinding\n411: metadata:\n412:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n413:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n414: roleRef:\n415:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n416:   kind: Role\n417:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n418: subjects:\n419: - kind: ServiceAccount\n420:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n421:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n422: ```\n423: \n424: #### Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n425: \n426: Rendered only when `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`:\n427: \n428: ```yaml\n429: # ServiceAccount\n430: apiVersion: v1\n431: kind: ServiceAccount\n432: metadata:\n433:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n434: \n435: # ConfigMap\n436: apiVersion: v1\n437: kind: ConfigMap\n438: metadata:\n439:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap\n440: data:\n441:   agent-scheduler.conf: |\n442:     actions: \"allocate\"\n443:     tiers:\n444:     - plugins:\n445:       - name: predicates\n446:       - name: nodeorder\n447: \n448: # ClusterRole with comprehensive scheduling permissions\n449: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n450: kind: ClusterRole\n451: metadata:\n452:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n453: rules:\n454: # CRD management\n455: - apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]\n456:   resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]\n457:   verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n458: \n459: # Core resources\n460: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n461:   resources: [\"events\", \"pods\", \"pods/status\", \"pods/binding\"]\n462:   verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n463: # ... (additional pod-related permissions)\n464: \n465: # Deployment\n466: apiVersion: apps/v1\n467: kind: Deployment\n468: metadata:\n469:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n470: spec:\n471:   replicas: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.replicas }}\n472:   template:\n473:     spec:\n474:       serviceAccountName: volcano-agent-scheduler\n475:       containers:\n476:       - name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n477:         image: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.image.tag }}\n478:         args:\n479:         - --scheduler-name=agent-scheduler\n480:         - --config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf\n481:         securityContext:\n482:           runAsNonRoot: true\n483:           runAsUser: 1000\n484:         volumeMounts:\n485:         - name: config\n486:           mountPath: /config\n487:         - name: empty\n488:           mountPath: /emptydir\n489:       volumes:\n490:       - name: config\n491:         configMap:\n492:           name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap\n493:       - name: empty\n494:         emptyDir: {}\n495: ```\n496: \n497: ### CRD Definitions\n498: \n499: #### AgentRuntime CRD\n500: \n501: ```yaml\n502: apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\n503: kind: CustomResourceDefinition\n504: metadata:\n505:   name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n506: spec:\n507:   group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n508:   names:\n509:     kind: AgentRuntime\n510:     plural: agentruntimes\n511:     shortNames: [ar]\n512:     singular: agentruntime\n513:   scope: Namespaced\n514:   versions:\n515:   - name: v1alpha1\n516:     served: true\n517:     storage: true\n518:     additionalPrinterColumns:\n519:     - name: NAME\n520:       type: string\n521:       jsonPath: .metadata.name\n522:     - name: PHASE\n523:       type: string\n524:       jsonPath: .status.phase\n525:     - name: SANDBOX\n526:       type: string\n527:       jsonPath: .status.sandboxRef.name\n528:     - name: AGE\n529:       type: date\n530:       jsonPath: .metadata.creationTimestamp\n531:     schema:\n532:       openAPIV3Schema:\n533:         type: object\n534:         properties:\n535:           spec:\n536:             required:\n537:             - maxSessionDuration\n538:             - podTemplate\n539:             - sessionTimeout\n540:             - targetPort\n541:             properties:\n542:               maxSessionDuration:\n543:                 type: string\n544:                 default: \"8h\"\n545:               sessionTimeout:\n546:                 type: string\n547:                 default: \"15m\"\n548:               targetPort:\n549:                 type: array\n550:                 items:\n551:                   type: object\n552:                   required: [port, protocol]\n553:                   properties:\n554:                     port:\n555:                       type: integer\n556:                     protocol:\n557:                       type: string\n558:                       enum: [HTTP, HTTPS]\n559:               podTemplate:\n560:                 type: object\n561:                 # Full PodSpec-like schema\n562: ```\n563: \n564: #### CodeInterpreter CRD\n565: \n566: ```yaml\n567: apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\n568: kind: CustomResourceDefinition\n569: metadata:\n570:   name: codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n571: spec:\n572:   group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n573:   names:\n574:     kind: CodeInterpreter\n575:     plural: codeinterpreters\n576:     shortNames: [ci]\n577:     singular: codeinterpreter\n578:   scope: Namespaced\n579:   versions:\n580:   - name: v1alpha1\n581:     served: true\n582:     storage: true\n583:     subresources:\n584:       status: {}\n585:     schema:\n586:       openAPIV3Schema:\n587:         type: object\n588:         properties:\n589:           spec:\n590:             required: [template]\n591:             properties:\n592:               authMode:\n593:                 type: string\n594:                 enum: [picod, none]\n595:                 default: picod\n596:               maxSessionDuration:\n597:                 type: string\n598:                 default: \"8h\"\n599:               sessionTimeout:\n600:                 type: string\n601:                 default: \"15m\"\n602:               warmPoolSize:\n603:                 type: integer\n604:                 format: int32\n605:               template:\n606:                 type: object\n607:                 # Container template schema\n608: ```\n609: \n610: ## Error Handling\n611: \n612: ### Chart Validation Errors\n613: \n614: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n615: |-------|-----------|---------|\n616: | Chart validation failure | 1 | `helm lint failed: {detail}` |\n617: | Template render failure | 1 | `helm template failed: {detail}` |\n618: | CRD installation failure | 1 | `Failed to install CRD: {detail}` |\n619: | Redis address not provided | 1 | `redis.addr is required in values` |\n620: | Invalid YAML syntax | 1 | `YAML parse error in {file}: {detail}` |\n621: \n622: ### Runtime Errors\n623: \n624: | Error | Component | Recovery |\n625: |-------|-----------|----------|\n626: | Redis connection refused | Router, WorkloadManager | Retry with exponential backoff |\n627: | Invalid Redis password | Router, WorkloadManager | Log error, fail health check |\n628: | RBAC permission denied | WorkloadManager | Log error, fail reconciliation |\n629: | CRD not found | All components | Fail startup, require manual CRD install |\n630: \n631: ## Testing Strategy\n632: \n633: ### Unit Tests\n634: \n635: **Location**: `manifests/charts/base/tests/` (to be created)\n636: \n637: ```yaml\n638: # tests/workloadmanager_test.yaml\n639: suite: WorkloadManager Deployment tests\n640: tests:\n641:   - it: creates Deployment with correct metadata\n642:     asserts:\n643:       - hasDocuments:\n644:           count: 1\n645:         documentIndex: 0\n646:         isKind:\n647:           of: Deployment\n648:       - equal:\n649:           path: metadata.name\n650:           value: workloadmanager\n651: \n652:   - it: sets replicas from values\n653:     set:\n654:       workloadmanager.replicas: 3\n655:     asserts:\n656:       - equal:\n657:           path: spec.replicas\n658:           value: 3\n659: \n660:   - it: injects correct environment variables\n661:     asserts:\n662:       - contains:\n663:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].env\n664:           content:\n665:             name: REDIS_ADDR\n666:             value: \"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\"\n667: \n668:   - it: configures liveness probe correctly\n669:     asserts:\n670:       - equal:\n671:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].livenessProbe.httpGet.path\n672:           value: /health\n673:       - equal:\n674:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].livenessProbe.initialDelaySeconds\n675:           value: 10\n676: \n677:   - it: applies resource limits from values\n678:     set:\n679:       workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 1000m\n680:       workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 1Gi\n681:     asserts:\n682:       - equal:\n683:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.limits.cpu\n684:           value: 1000m\n685: ```\n686: \n687: ### Integration Tests\n688: \n689: **Command**: `helm template test manifests/charts/base`\n690: \n691: Verify:\n692: 1. All templates render without errors\n693: 2. Generated YAML is valid\n694: 3. Conditional resources respect flags\n695: 4. Values overrides work correctly\n696: \n697: **Command**: `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n698: \n699: Verify:\n700: 1. No linting errors or warnings\n701: 2. Chart structure is valid\n702: 3. All required files present\n703: \n704: ### E2E Tests\n705: \n706: **Scenario**: Full chart installation in Kind cluster\n707: \n708: ```bash\n709: # Create Kind cluster\n710: kind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n711: \n712: # Install chart\n713: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n714:   --namespace agentcube \\\n715:   --create-namespace \\\n716:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n717:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n718:   --wait\n719: \n720: # Verify deployments are ready\n721: kubectl wait deployment/workloadmanager --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n722: kubectl wait deployment/agentcube-router --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n723: \n724: # Verify services are created\n725: kubectl get svc -n agentcube\n726: \n727: # Test with optional components\n728: helm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n729:   --namespace agentcube \\\n730:   --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true \\\n731:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n732:   --wait\n733: \n734: # Verify optional components\n735: kubectl wait deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n736: kubectl get clusterrole/workloadmanager\n737: kubectl get role/agentcube-router --namespace=agentcube\n738: \n739: # Cleanup\n740: kind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n741: ```\n742: \n743: ## Dependencies\n744: \n745: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n746: |---------|---------|---------|\n747: | Helm | ≥3.0.0 | Chart packaging and deployment |\n748: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | API compatibility |\n749: | Redis | Any | External dependency (session storage) |\n750: | Volcano | Optional | Advanced scheduling (if enabled) |\n751: \n752: ## File Structure\n753: \n754: ```\n755: manifests/\n756: └── charts/\n757:     └── base/\n758:         ├── Chart.yaml                    # REQUIRED: Chart metadata\n759:         ├── values.yaml                   # REQUIRED: Default configuration\n760:         ├── .helmignore                   # REQUIRED: Packaging exclusions\n761:         ├── crds/\n762:         │   ├── agentruntime.yaml         # EXISTING: AgentRuntime CRD\n763:         │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml      # NEW: CodeInterpreter CRD\n764:         └── templates/\n765:             ├── _helpers.tpl              # Helper templates\n766:             ├── redis-secret.yaml         # Redis password Secret\n767:             ├── workloadmanager.yaml      # WorkloadManager Deployment + Service\n768:             ├── agentcube-router.yaml     # Router Deployment + Service\n769:             ├── rbac/\n770:             │   └── workloadmanager.yaml  # WorkloadManager RBAC\n771:             ├── rbac-router.yaml          # Optional Router RBAC\n772:             └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano Scheduler\n773: ```\n774: \n775: ## Multi-Environment Support\n776: \n777: ### Development Environment\n778: \n779: ```yaml\n780: # values-dev.yaml\n781: router:\n782:   replicas: 1\n783:   resources:\n784:     limits:\n785:       cpu: 250m\n786:       memory: 256Mi\n787:     requests:\n788:       cpu: 50m\n789:       memory: 64Mi\n790: \n791: workloadmanager:\n792:   replicas: 1\n793:   resources:\n794:     limits:\n795:       cpu: 250m\n796:       memory: 256Mi\n797:     requests:\n798:       cpu: 50m\n799:       memory: 64Mi\n800: \n801: volcano:\n802:   scheduler:\n803:     enabled: false\n804: ```\n805: \n806: ### Production Environment\n807: \n808: ```yaml\n809: # values-prod.yaml\n810: router:\n811:   replicas: 3\n812:   resources:\n813:     limits:\n814:       cpu: 1000m\n815:       memory: 1Gi\n816:     requests:\n817:       cpu: 200m\n818:       memory: 256Mi\n819: \n820: workloadmanager:\n821:   replicas: 2\n822:   resources:\n823:     limits:\n824:       cpu: 1000m\n825:       memory: 1Gi\n826:     requests:\n827:       cpu: 200m\n828:       memory: 256Mi\n829: \n830: volcano:\n831:   scheduler:\n832:     enabled: true\n833:     replicas: 2\n834: ```\n835: \n836: ### Usage\n837: \n838: ```bash\n839: # Development\n840: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base -f values-dev.yaml \\\n841:   --set redis.addr=redis-dev:6379\n842: \n843: # Production\n844: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base -f values-prod.yaml \\\n845:   --set redis.addr=redis-prod:6379\n846: \n847: # Custom image registry\n848: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n849:   --set router.image.repository=myregistry.com/agentcube-router \\\n850:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=myregistry.com/workloadmanager\n851: ```\n852: \n853: ## Acceptance Checklist\n854: \n855: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` — Chart metadata with correct apiVersion, name, version\n856: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` — Complete configuration tree for all components\n857: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with correct env/probes\n858: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n859: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n860: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` — Conditional Router RBAC\n861: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — Conditional Volcano Scheduler\n862: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml` — Redis password Secret\n863: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml` — AgentRuntime CRD (existing, verify completeness)\n864: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml` — CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n865: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore` — Ignore patterns for packaging\n866: - [ ] `helm lint` passes without errors\n867: - [ ] `helm template` generates valid YAML\n868: - [ ] `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n869: - [ ] Optional components render correctly when enabled/disabled\n870: - [ ] Values overrides work correctly for multi-environment support\n871: \n872: ## Open Questions\n873: \n874: 1. **External Redis Operator Integration**: Should the chart support automatic Redis provisioning via Redis Operator (e.g., Spotahome, OperatorHub)?\n875: \n876: 2. **Monitoring and Logging**: Should Prometheus scrape annotations, ServiceMonitor CRs, and Fluentd/ELK integration be included in the chart?\n877: \n878: 3. **Multi-Cluster Deployment**: Should the chart support deployment across multiple Kubernetes clusters with shared Redis backend?\n879: \n880: 4. **Default Values for Development**: Should the chart include a `values-dev.yaml` file with development-appropriate defaults out of the box?\n881: \n882: 5. **Ingress Configuration**: Should an Ingress resource be added for external access to Router and WorkloadManager services?\n883: \n884: 6. **Pod Disruption Budgets**: Should PDBs be configured for production deployments to ensure availability during node maintenance?\n\n(End of file - total 884 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-030 Helm Chart Templates and Values\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the AgentCube Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`). The chart packages and deploys all AgentCube control plane components including Router, WorkloadManager, and optional Volcano Agent Scheduler with support for multi-environment configurations.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Chart Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata (apiVersion, name, version)\n├── values.yaml                         # Configuration values tree\n├── .helmignore                         # Packaging exclusion patterns\n├── crds/\n│   ├── agentruntime.yaml               # AgentRuntime CRD (existing)\n│   └── codeinterpreter.yaml            # CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n└── templates/\n    ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helper functions","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md","time":{"start":1775880101924,"end":1775880101957}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880101963,"sessionID":"ses_2854c6defffeP8kJpwKqyO4d3V","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab3d080001r7Ty1NGF2xns5u","messageID":"msg_d7ab3b6a1001axoBL0DzZus01C","sessionID":"ses_2854c6defffeP8kJpwKqyO4d3V","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_eded22a7c5b94a13beedb24f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `manifests`  \n6: **Language:** YAML  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Standalone RBAC manifests for ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** manifests/delta-spec.md (AR-030), manifests/design.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-031.1: ServiceAccount Manifests\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ServiceAccount manifests for WorkloadManager, Router, and Volcano Scheduler components.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation\n21: - **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n22: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n23: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount metadata\n26: - **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n27: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n29:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n30:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n31:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount creation\n34: - **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/router.yaml` is applied\n35: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/router.yaml` is executed\n36: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount metadata\n39: - **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n40: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n41: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n42:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n43:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n44:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount creation\n47: - **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n48: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n49: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount metadata\n52: - **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n53: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n55:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n56:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n57:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: volcano-agent-scheduler`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: scheduler`\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ### REQ-031.2: ClusterRole Manifests\n62: \n63: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ClusterRole manifests defining permissions for WorkloadManager and Volcano Scheduler.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole creation\n66: - **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n67: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n68: - **THEN** a ClusterRole named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole sandbox permissions\n71: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n72: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n74:   - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n75:   - `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`\n76:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole extension resources\n79: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n80: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n82:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n83:   - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n84:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole warm pool status\n87: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n88: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n90:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n91:   - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n92:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n95: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n96: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n98:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n99:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n100:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n101:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n102:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`, `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n105: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n106: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n107: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n108:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n109:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n110:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n111:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n112:   - `verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole core resources\n115: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n116: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n117: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n118:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n119:   - `resources: [\"pods\", \"secrets\"]`\n120:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole token review\n123: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n124: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n125: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n126:   - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n127:   - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n128:   - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole creation\n131: - **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n132: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n133: - **THEN** a ClusterRole named `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL be created\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole CRD permissions\n136: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n137: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n138: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n139:   - `apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]`\n140:   - `resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]`\n141:   - `verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole pod permissions\n144: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n145: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL include comprehensive pod permissions:\n147:   - `resources: [\"pods\", \"pods/status\", \"pods/binding\", \"pods/disruptionbudgets\"]`\n148:   - `resources: [\"persistentvolumeclaims\", \"persistentvolumes\"]`\n149:   - `resources: [\"nodes\", \"namespaces\", \"services\", \"replicationcontrollers\"]`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole scheduling permissions\n152: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n153: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n154: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n155:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.k8s.io\"]`\n156:   - `resources: [\"priorityclasses\"]`\n157:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n158:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.incubator.k8s.io\", \"scheduling.volcano.sh\"]`\n159:   - `resources: [\"podgroups\"]`\n160:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\", \"update\"]`\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole storage permissions\n163: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n164: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n165: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n166:   - `apiGroups: [\"storage.k8s.io\"]`\n167:   - `resources: [\"storageclasses\", \"csinodes\", \"csidrivers\", \"csistoragecapacities\", \"volumeattachments\"]`\n168:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\"]`\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole configmap permissions\n171: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n172: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n173: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n174:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n175:   - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n176:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"delete\", \"update\"]`\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ### REQ-031.3: ClusterRoleBinding Manifests\n181: \n182: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ClusterRoleBinding manifests binding ClusterRoles to ServiceAccounts.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding creation\n185: - **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n186: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n187: - **THEN** a ClusterRoleBinding named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding subject\n190: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n191: - **WHEN** subjects are validated\n192: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n193:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n194:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n195:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding roleRef\n198: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n199: - **WHEN** roleRef is validated\n200: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n201:   - `kind: ClusterRole`\n202:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n203:   - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding creation\n206: - **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n207: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n208: - **THEN** a ClusterRoleBinding named `volcano-agent-scheduler-role` SHALL be created\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding subject\n211: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n212: - **WHEN** subjects are validated\n213: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n214:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n215:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n216:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding roleRef\n219: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n220: - **WHEN** roleRef is validated\n221: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n222:   - `kind: ClusterRole`\n223:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n224:   - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ### REQ-031.4: Role Manifests (Namespace-Scoped)\n229: \n230: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide namespace-scoped Role manifests for Router component.\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Router Role creation\n233: - **GIVEN** the manifest `roles/router.yaml` is applied\n234: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f roles/router.yaml` is executed\n235: - **THEN** a Role named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Router Role secret permissions\n238: - **GIVEN** the Role is created\n239: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n240: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n241:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n242:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n243:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Router Role configmap permissions\n246: - **GIVEN** the Role is created\n247: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n248: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n249:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n250:   - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n251:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Router Role pod permissions\n254: - **GIVEN** the Role is created\n255: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n256: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n257:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n258:   - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n259:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ### REQ-031.5: RoleBinding Manifests (Namespace-Scoped)\n264: \n265: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RoleBinding manifests binding Roles to ServiceAccounts.\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding creation\n268: - **GIVEN** the manifest `rolebindings/router.yaml` is applied\n269: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f rolebindings/router.yaml` is executed\n270: - **THEN** a RoleBinding named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding subject\n273: - **GIVEN** the RoleBinding is created\n274: - **WHEN** subjects are validated\n275: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n276:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n277:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n278:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding roleRef\n281: - **GIVEN** the RoleBinding is created\n282: - **WHEN** roleRef is validated\n283: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n284:   - `kind: Role`\n285:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n286:   - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n287: \n288: ---\n289: \n290: ### REQ-031.6: Namespace Management\n291: \n292: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide namespace manifest and support namespace creation before RBAC application.\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Namespace manifest creation\n295: - **GIVEN** the manifest `namespace.yaml` is applied\n296: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml` is executed\n297: - **THEN** a namespace named `agentcube-system` SHALL be created\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Namespace metadata\n300: - **GIVEN** the namespace is created\n301: - **WHEN** namespace is validated\n302: - **THEN** it SHALL include labels:\n303:   - `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube`\n304:   - `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: Custom namespace support\n307: - **GIVEN** user wants to use custom namespace\n308: - **WHEN** manifests are applied with `--namespace` flag\n309: - **THEN** all RBAC resources SHALL be created in the specified namespace\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Default namespace fallback\n312: - **GIVEN** no namespace is specified\n313: - **WHEN** manifests are applied\n314: - **THEN** resources SHALL be created in `agentcube-system` namespace (from manifest) or `default` namespace\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ### REQ-031.7: Combined RBAC Manifest\n319: \n320: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a combined RBAC manifest that applies all RBAC resources in correct order.\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: Combined manifest existence\n323: - **GIVEN** the manifest `rbac.yaml` exists\n324: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f rbac.yaml` is executed\n325: - **THEN** all ServiceAccounts, ClusterRoles, ClusterRoleBindings, Roles, and RoleBindings SHALL be created\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Correct resource ordering\n328: - **GIVEN** the combined manifest is applied\n329: - **WHEN** resources are created\n330: - **THEN** order SHALL be:\n331:   1. ServiceAccounts\n332:   2. ClusterRoles\n333:   3. ClusterRoleBindings\n334:   4. Roles\n335:   5. RoleBindings\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: Combined manifest labels\n338: - **GIVEN** the combined manifest is applied\n339: - **WHEN** resources are created\n340: - **THEN** all resources SHALL include common label:\n341:   - `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ### REQ-031.8: RBAC Validation and Verification\n346: \n347: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide validation scripts and commands to verify RBAC configuration.\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: RBAC validation script\n350: - **GIVEN** the script `validate-rbac.sh` exists\n351: - **WHEN** `./validate-rbac.sh` is executed\n352: - **THEN** script SHALL verify all ServiceAccounts exist\n353: \n354: #### Scenario: ClusterRole permissions check\n355: - **GIVEN** the validation script is executed\n356: - **WHEN** ClusterRoles are checked\n357: - **THEN** script SHALL verify all required permissions are present\n358: \n359: #### Scenario: Binding verification\n360: - **GIVEN** the validation script is executed\n361: - **WHEN** bindings are checked\n362: - **THEN** script SHALL verify all ServiceAccounts are bound to correct roles\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: RBAC verification report\n365: - **GIVEN** the validation script completes\n366: - **WHEN** report is generated\n367: - **THEN** output SHALL include:\n368:   - List of all ServiceAccounts\n369:   - List of all ClusterRoles with permission counts\n370:   - List of all bindings with subjects\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ### REQ-031.9: Multi-Namespace Support\n375: \n376: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support deploying RBAC for multiple namespaces.\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: Multi-namespace ServiceAccount\n379: - **GIVEN** manifests are applied to multiple namespaces\n380: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/ -n namespace1` and `-n namespace2` are executed\n381: - **THEN** ServiceAccounts SHALL be created in both namespaces\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: ClusterRole reuse across namespaces\n384: - **GIVEN** ClusterRoles are cluster-scoped\n385: - **WHEN** multiple namespaces use the same Component\n386: - **THEN** single ClusterRole SHALL be shared across namespaces\n387: \n388: #### Scenario: Namespace-specific RoleBindings\n389: - **GIVEN** multiple namespaces are configured\n390: - **WHEN** RoleBindings are created\n391: - **THEN** each namespace SHALL have its own RoleBinding referencing namespace-specific ServiceAccount\n392: \n393: ---\n394: \n395: ### REQ-031.10: RBAC Cleanup\n396: \n397: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide cleanup manifests and scripts to remove RBAC resources.\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: RBAC cleanup manifest\n400: - **GIVEN** the manifest `rbac-cleanup.yaml` exists\n401: - **WHEN** `kubectl delete -f rbac-cleanup.yaml` is executed\n402: - **THEN** all RBAC resources SHALL be deleted\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Correct cleanup ordering\n405: - **GIVEN** cleanup is executed\n406: - **WHEN** resources are deleted\n407: - **THEN** order SHALL be:\n408:   1. RoleBindings\n409:   2. Roles\n410:   3. ClusterRoleBindings\n411:   4. ClusterRoles\n412:   5. ServiceAccounts\n413: \n414: #### Scenario: Namespace-preserved cleanup\n415: - **GIVEN** cleanup is executed with `--preserve-namespace`\n416: - **WHEN** resources are deleted\n417: - **THEN** namespace SHALL NOT be deleted, only RBAC resources\n418: \n419: ---\n420: \n421: ## Data Types\n422: \n423: ```yaml\n424: # ServiceAccount structure\n425: serviceAccount:\n426:   apiVersion: v1\n427:   kind: ServiceAccount\n428:   metadata:\n429:     name: string\n430:     namespace: string\n431:     labels:\n432:       app.kubernetes.io/name: string\n433:       app.kubernetes.io/component: string\n434: \n435: # ClusterRole structure\n436: clusterRole:\n437:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n438:   kind: ClusterRole\n439:   metadata:\n440:     name: string\n441:   rules:\n442:     - apiGroups: [string]\n443:       resources: [string]\n444:       verbs: [string]\n445: \n446: # ClusterRoleBinding structure\n447: clusterRoleBinding:\n448:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n449:   kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n450:   metadata:\n451:     name: string\n452:   roleRef:\n453:     kind: ClusterRole\n454:     name: string\n455:     apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n456:   subjects:\n457:     - kind: ServiceAccount\n458:       name: string\n459:       namespace: string\n460: \n461: # Role structure (namespace-scoped)\n462: role:\n463:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n464:   kind: Role\n465:   metadata:\n466:     name: string\n467:     namespace: string\n468:   rules:\n469:     - apiGroups: [string]\n470:       resources: [string]\n471:       verbs: [string]\n472: \n473: # RoleBinding structure (namespace-scoped)\n474: roleBinding:\n475:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n476:   kind: RoleBinding\n477:   metadata:\n478:     name: string\n479:     namespace: string\n480:   roleRef:\n481:     kind: Role\n482:     name: string\n483:     apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n484:   subjects:\n485:     - kind: ServiceAccount\n486:       name: string\n487:       namespace: string\n488: ```\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ## File Structure\n493: \n494: ```\n495: manifests/rbac/\n496: ├── README.md\n497: ├── namespace.yaml\n498: ├── serviceaccounts/\n499: │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n500: │   ├── router.yaml\n501: │   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n502: ├── clusterroles/\n503: │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n504: │   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n505: ├── clusterrolebindings/\n506: │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n507: │   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n508: ├── roles/\n509: │   └── router.yaml\n510: ├── rolebindings/\n511: │   └── router.yaml\n512: ├── rbac.yaml              # Combined manifest\n513: ├── rbac-cleanup.yaml      # Cleanup manifest\n514: └── validate-rbac.sh       # Validation script\n515: ```\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ## Environment Variables\n520: \n521: | Variable | Description | Default |\n522: |----------|-------------|---------|\n523: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Target namespace for RBAC resources | `agentcube-system` |\n524: | `KUBECONFIG` | Kubernetes config file | `~/.kube/config` |\n525: \n526: ---\n527: \n528: ## Error Codes\n529: \n530: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n531: |-------|-----------|---------|\n532: | Namespace not found | 1 | `Namespace '{namespace}' does not exist. Run: kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml` |\n533: | ServiceAccount not found | 1 | `ServiceAccount '{name}' not found in namespace '{namespace}'` |\n534: | ClusterRole not found | 1 | `ClusterRole '{name}' not found` |\n535: | Binding failure | 1 | `Failed to bind {role} to {serviceAccount}: {detail}` |\n536: | Permission denied | 1 | `RBAC: User '{user}' cannot {verb} {resource}` |\n537: | Invalid manifest syntax | 1 | `YAML parse error in {file}: {detail}` |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Dependencies\n542: \n543: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n544: |---------|---------|---------|\n545: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | RBAC API (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n546: | kubectl | ≥1.21 | Manifest application and validation |\n547: \n548: ---\n549: \n550: ## Acceptance Checklist\n551: \n552: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/namespace.yaml` — Namespace manifest with correct labels\n553: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n554: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/router.yaml` — Router ServiceAccount\n555: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount\n556: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRole with all permissions\n557: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole with scheduling permissions\n558: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n559: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n560: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/roles/router.yaml` — Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n561: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/rolebindings/router.yaml` — Router RoleBinding\n562: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac.yaml` — Combined manifest with correct ordering\n563: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac-cleanup.yaml` — Cleanup manifest with reverse ordering\n564: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/validate-rbac.sh` — Validation script\n565: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/README.md` — Usage documentation\n566: - [ ] `kubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/` succeeds without errors\n567: - [ ] Validation script reports all resources as healthy\n568: - [ ] Cleanup removes all RBAC resources correctly\n569: - [ ] Multi-namespace deployment works correctly\n570: \n571: ---\n572: \n573: ## Open Questions\n574: \n575: 1. Should RBAC manifests support fine-grained permission customization through overlay files?\n576: 2. Should the validation script integrate with CI/CD pipelines for automated RBAC testing?\n577: 3. Should RBAC manifests include PodSecurityPolicy or PodSecurityStandard bindings?\n578: 4. Should there be separate RBAC profiles (minimal, standard, full) for different security requirements?\n\n(End of file - total 578 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Standalone RBAC manifests for ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding\n\n**Base Specs:** manifests/delta-spec.md (AR-030), manifests/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-031.1: ServiceAccount Manifests\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ServiceAccount manifests for WorkloadManager, Router, and Volcano Scheduler components.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775880101928,"end":1775880101960}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880101967,"sessionID":"ses_2854c6defffeP8kJpwKqyO4d3V","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab3db0f001qZy6jXt4Bvkheb","messageID":"msg_d7ab3b6a1001axoBL0DzZus01C","sessionID":"ses_2854c6defffeP8kJpwKqyO4d3V","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5f197ac215574ec183f78de1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n2: apiVersion: v1\n3: kind: ServiceAccount\n4: metadata:\n5:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n6:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n7: ---\n8: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n9: kind: Role\n10: metadata:\n11:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n12:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n13: rules:\n14:   - apiGroups:\n15:       - \"\"\n16:     resources:\n17:       - secrets\n18:     verbs:\n19:       - get\n20:       - list\n21:       - watch\n22:       - create\n23:       - update\n24:       - patch\n25:       - delete\n26: ---\n27: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n28: kind: RoleBinding\n29: metadata:\n30:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n31:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n32: roleRef:\n33:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n34:   kind: Role\n35:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n36: subjects:\n37:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n38:     name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n39:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n40: {{- end }}\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\nrules:\n  - apiGroups:\n      - \"\"\n    resources:\n      - secrets\n    verbs:\n      - get\n      - list","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml","time":{"start":1775880101932,"end":1775880101966}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880101987,"sessionID":"ses_2854c6defffeP8kJpwKqyO4d3V","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab3d590001wEcwMwJv4xsidC","messageID":"msg_d7ab3b6a1001axoBL0DzZus01C","sessionID":"ses_2854c6defffeP8kJpwKqyO4d3V","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_96a8857805964d4097e8f030","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: apiVersion: v1\n2: kind: ServiceAccount\n3: metadata:\n4:   name: workloadmanager\n5:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n6: ---\n7: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n8: kind: ClusterRole\n9: metadata:\n10:   name: workloadmanager\n11: rules:\n12:   - apiGroups:\n13:       - agents.x-k8s.io\n14:     resources:\n15:       - sandboxes\n16:     verbs:\n17:       - get\n18:       - list\n19:       - watch\n20:       - create\n21:       - update\n22:       - patch\n23:       - delete\n24:   - apiGroups:\n25:       - extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\n26:     resources:\n27:       - sandboxclaims\n28:     verbs:\n29:       - get\n30:       - list\n31:       - watch\n32:       - create\n33:       - update\n34:       - patch\n35:       - delete\n36:   - apiGroups:\n37:       - extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\n38:     resources:\n39:       - sandboxtemplates\n40:     verbs:\n41:       - get\n42:       - list\n43:       - watch\n44:       - create\n45:       - update\n46:       - patch\n47:       - delete\n48:   - apiGroups:\n49:       - extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\n50:     resources:\n51:       - sandboxwarmpools\n52:     verbs:\n53:       - get\n54:       - list\n55:       - watch\n56:       - create\n57:       - update\n58:       - patch\n59:       - delete\n60:   - apiGroups:\n61:       - extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\n62:     resources:\n63:       - sandboxwarmpools/status\n64:     verbs:\n65:       - get\n66:       - update\n67:       - patch\n68:   - apiGroups:\n69:       - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n70:     resources:\n71:       - codeinterpreters\n72:     verbs:\n73:       - get\n74:       - list\n75:       - watch\n76:       - create\n77:       - update\n78:       - patch\n79:       - delete\n80:   - apiGroups:\n81:       - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n82:     resources:\n83:       - codeinterpreters/status\n84:     verbs:\n85:       - get\n86:       - update\n87:       - patch\n88:   - apiGroups:\n89:       - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n90:     resources:\n91:       - codeinterpreters/finalizers\n92:     verbs:\n93:       - update\n94:   - apiGroups:\n95:       - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n96:     resources:\n97:       - agentruntimes\n98:     verbs:\n99:       - get\n100:       - list\n101:       - watch\n102:   - apiGroups:\n103:       - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n104:     resources:\n105:       - agentruntimes/status\n106:     verbs:\n107:       - update\n108:       - patch\n109:   - apiGroups:\n110:       - \"\"\n111:     resources:\n112:       - pods\n113:     verbs:\n114:       - get\n115:       - list\n116:       - watch\n117:   - apiGroups:\n118:       - authentication.k8s.io\n119:     resources:\n120:       - tokenreviews\n121:     verbs:\n122:       - create\n123:   - apiGroups:\n124:       - \"\"\n125:     resources:\n126:       - secrets\n127:     verbs:\n128:       - get\n129:       - list\n130:       - watch\n131:       - create\n132:       - update\n133:       - patch\n134:       - delete\n135: ---\n136: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n137: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n138: metadata:\n139:   name: workloadmanager\n140: roleRef:\n141:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n142:   kind: ClusterRole\n143:   name: workloadmanager\n144: subjects:\n145:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n146:     name: workloadmanager\n147:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n\n(End of file - total 147 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"apiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\n  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\nrules:\n  - apiGroups:\n      - agents.x-k8s.io\n    resources:\n      - sandboxes\n    verbs:\n      - get\n      - list\n      - watch\n      - create","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml","time":{"start":1775880101930,"end":1775880101985}}}}
