es in correct dependency order:\n\n```yaml\n# Source: namespace.yaml\n---\n# Source: serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml\n---\n# Source: serviceaccounts/router.yaml\n---\n# Source: serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml\n---\n# Source: clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml\n---\n# Source: clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml\n---\n# Source: clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml\n---\n# Source: clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml\n---\n# Source: roles/router.yaml\n---\n# Source: rolebindings/router.yaml\n```\n\nEach resource includes a `# Source:` comment for traceability.\n\n### Cleanup Manifest\n\nThe `rbac-cleanup.yaml` file contains all resources in reverse order for proper deletion:\n\n```yaml\n# Source: rolebindings/router.yaml\n---\n# Source: roles/router.yaml\n---\n# Source: clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml\n---\n# Source: clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml\n---\n# Source: clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml\n---\n# Source: clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml\n---\n# Source: serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml\n---\n# Source: serviceaccounts/router.yaml\n---\n# Source: serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml\n---\n# Source: namespace.yaml (optional, commented out by default)\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Manifest Validation Errors\n\n| Error | Exit Code | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Invalid YAML syntax | 1 | `YAML parse error in {file}: {detail}` |\n| Missing required field | 1 | `Missing required field '{field}' in {file}` |\n| Invalid API version | 1 | `Unsupported API version '{version}' in {file}` |\n| Invalid kind | 1 | `Unknown resource kind '{kind}' in {file}` |\n\n### Application Errors\n\n| Error | Exit Code | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Namespace not found | 1 | `Namespace '{namespace}' does not exist. Run: kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml` |\n| ServiceAccount not found | 1 | `ServiceAccount '{name}' not found in namespace '{namespace}'` |\n| ClusterRole not found | 1 | `ClusterRole '{name}' 