ion script (optional) |\n| Bash | ≥4.0 | Shell scripts |\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/rbac/\n├── README.md                       # Usage documentation\n├── namespace.yaml                  # Namespace: agentcube-system\n├── serviceaccounts/\n│   ├── workloadmanager.yaml        # ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager\n│   ├── router.yaml                 # ServiceAccount for Router\n│   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml      # ServiceAccount for Volcano Scheduler\n├── clusterroles/\n│   ├── workloadmanager.yaml        # ClusterRole with sandbox/CR permissions\n│   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml      # ClusterRole with scheduling permissions\n├── clusterrolebindings/\n│   ├── workloadmanager.yaml        # Binds workloadmanager SA to ClusterRole\n│   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml      # Binds volcano-scheduler SA to ClusterRole\n├── roles/\n│   └── router.yaml                 # Role with secret/configmap permissions\n├── rolebindings/\n│   └── router.yaml                 # Binds router SA to Role\n├── rbac.yaml                       # Combined manifest (install order)\n├── rbac-cleanup.yaml               # Cleanup manifest (uninstall order)\n├── validate-rbac.sh                # Validation script\n└── tests/\n    ├── validate-manifests.sh       # YAML syntax validation\n    ├── test-dry-run.sh             # kubectl dry-run tests\n    ├── test-validate.sh            # Validation script test\n    ├── test-cleanup.sh             # Cleanup test\n    └── integration/\n        └── test-e2e.sh             # E2E integration test\n```\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | No | `agentcube-system` | Target namespace for RBAC resources |\n| `KUBECONFIG` | No | `~/.kube/config` | Kubernetes config file |\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Quick Start (Combined Manifest)\n\n```bash\n# Create namespace and apply all RBAC resources\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/rbac.yaml\n\n# Verify resources\nkubectl get serviceaccounts -n agentcube-system\nkubectl get clusterroles | grep -E 'workloadmanager|volcano-agent-scheduler'\nkubectl get clusterrolebindings | grep -E 'workloadmanager|volcano-agent-scheduler'\nkubectl get role -n agentcube-system\nkubectl get rolebinding -n agentcube-system\n```\n\n### Step-by-Step Installation\n\n```bash\n# 1. Create namespace\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/namespace.yaml\n\n# 2. Create ServiceAccounts\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/\n\n# 3. Create ClusterRoles\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/clusterroles/\n\n# 4. Create ClusterRoleBindings\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/\n\n# 5. Create Role (namespace-scoped)\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/roles/ -n agentcube-system\n\n# 6. Create RoleBinding\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/rolebindings/ -n agentcube-system\n```\n\n### Custom Namespace\n\n```bash\n# Apply to custom namespace\nexport CUSTOM_NAMESPACE=my-agents\nkubectl create namespace \"$CUSTOM_NAMESPACE\"\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/ -n \"$CUSTOM_NAMESPACE\"\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/clusterroles/\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/roles/ -n \"$CUSTOM_NAMESPACE\"\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/rolebindings/ -n \"$CUSTOM_NAMESPACE\"\n```\n\n### Validation\n\n```bash\n# Run validation script\n./manifests/rbac/validate-rbac.sh --namespace agentcube-system\n\n# Manual verification\nkubectl auth can-i get sandboxes --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube-system:workloadmanager\nkubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube-system:volcano-agent-scheduler\nkubectl auth can-i get secrets --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube-system:agentcube-router\n```\n\n### Cleanup\n\n```bash\n# Remove all RBAC resources (namespace preserved)\nkubectl delete -f manifests/rbac/rbac-cleanup.yaml\n\n# Remove namespace as well\nkubectl delete namespace agentcube-system\n```\n\n## Validation Script\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# manifests/rbac/validate-rbac.sh\n\nset -e\n\nNAMESPACE=\"${1:-agentcube-system}\"\n\necho \"Validating RBAC configuration in namespace: $NAMESPACE\"\n\n# Check ServiceAccounts\necho \"Checking ServiceAccounts...\"\nfor sa in workloadmanager agentcube-router volcano-agent-scheduler; do\n    if ! kubectl get serviceaccount \"$sa\" -n \"$NAMESPACE\" &>/dev/null; then\n        echo \"ERROR: ServiceAccount '$sa' not found in namespace '$NAMESPACE'\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    echo \"  ✓ ServiceAccount/$sa\"\ndone\n\n# Check ClusterRoles\necho \"Checking ClusterRoles...\"\nfor cr in workloadmanager volcano-agent-scheduler; do\n    if ! kubectl get clusterrole \"$cr\" &>/dev/null; then\n        echo \"ERROR: ClusterRole '$cr' not found\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    echo \"  ✓ ClusterRole/$cr\"\ndone\n\n# Check ClusterRoleBindings\necho \"Checking ClusterRoleBindings...\"\nfor crb in workloadmanager volcano-agent-scheduler-role; do\n    if ! kubectl get clusterrolebinding \"$crb\" &>/dev/null; then\n        echo \"ERROR: ClusterRoleBinding '$crb' not found\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    echo \"  ✓ ClusterRoleBinding/$crb\"\ndone\n\n# Check Role\necho \"Checking Role...\"\nif ! kubectl get role agentcube-router -n \"$NAMESPACE\" &>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Role 'agentcube-router' not found in namespace '$NAMESPACE'\"\n    exit 1\nfi\necho \"  ✓ Role/agentcube-router\"\n\n# Check RoleBinding\necho \"Checking RoleBinding...\"\nif ! kubectl get rolebinding agentcube-router -n \"$NAMESPACE\" &>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: RoleBinding 'agentcube-router' not found in namespace '$NAMESPACE'\"\n    exit 1\nfi\necho \"  ✓ RoleBinding/agentcube-router\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"✓ All RBAC resources validated successfully\"\n```\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/namespace.yaml` — Namespace manifest with correct labels\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/router.yaml` — Router ServiceAccount\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRole with all permissions\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole with scheduling permissions\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/roles/router.yaml` — Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/rolebindings/router.yaml` — Router RoleBinding\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac.yaml` — Combined manifest with correct ordering\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac-cleanup.yaml` — Cleanup manifest with reverse ordering\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/validate-rbac.sh` — Validation script\n- [ ] `manifests/rbac/README.md` — Usage documentation\n- [ ] `kubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/` succeeds without errors\n- [ ] Validation script reports all resources as healthy\n- [ ] Cleanup removes all RBAC resources correctly\n- [ ] Multi-namespace deployment works correctly\n- [ ] All YAML manifests pass syntax validation\n- [ ] kubectl dry-run validation passes for all manifests\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **PodSecurityPolicy Integration**: Should RBAC manifests include bindings for PodSecurityPolicy or PodSecurityStandard admission control?\n\n2. **Fine-Grained Permission Profiles**: Should there be separate RBAC profiles (minimal, standard, full) for different security requirements and deployment scenarios?\n\n3. **CI/CD Integration**: Should the validation script integrate with CI/CD pipelines for automated RBAC testing in pull requests?\n\n4. **Overlay Support**: Should RBAC manifests support Kustomize overlays for environment-specific customizations (e.g., custom namespaces, additional permissions)?\n\n5. **Audit Logging**: Should RBAC resources include annotations for audit logging and compliance tracking?\n\n6. **Multi-Cluster Deployment**: Should there be guidance or tooling for deploying RBAC across multiple Kubernetes clusters with shared configuration?\n\n## Migration from Helm Chart\n\nFor users migrating from Helm chart RBAC to standalone manifests:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Export current RBAC configuration\nkubectl get serviceaccount,clusterrole,clusterrolebinding,role,rolebinding \\\n  -l app.kubernetes.io/part-of=agentcube \\\n  -o yaml > current-rbac.yaml\n\n# 2. Review differences with standalone manifests\ndiff current-rbac.yaml manifests/rbac/rbac.yaml\n\n# 3. Apply standalone manifests (Helm will ignore them)\nkubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/rbac.yaml\n\n# 4. Optionally disable Helm RBAC\nhelm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=false \\\n  --reuse-values\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Least Privilege**: ClusterRoles grant minimum permissions required for component operation\n2. **Namespace Isolation**: Router uses namespace-scoped Role instead of ClusterRole\n3. **ServiceAccount Per Component**: Each component has dedicated ServiceAccount for auditability\n4. **No Wildcard Permissions**: All rules specify explicit apiGroups, resources, and verbs\n5. **Label-Based Management**: Standard labels enable easy resource discovery and cleanup\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml\">\nERROR [1:3] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [1:5] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [2:1] Unexpected scalar at node end\nERROR [2:11] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [2:13] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"v1\"\nERROR [3:1] Unexpected scalar token in Y